```python
item_dict = {"Asia":"Asia", "North America":'North America', 
             "European Union":"Europe","Europe":"Europe","Oceania":"Oceania",
             "Africa":"Africa", "South America":"South America",
             "Northern Cyprus":"Europe"}
```


```python
 def item_mapping(df, dictionary, colsource, coltarget):
    dict_keys = list(dictionary.keys())
    dict_values = list(dictionary.values())
    for x in range(len(dict_keys)):
        df.loc[df[colsource]==dict_keys[x], coltarget] = dict_values[x]
    return(df)
```


```python
item_mapping(df, item_dict, "location", "continent")
```

```python
 def mapping(df, dictionary, colsource, coltarget):
    dict_keys = list(dictionary.keys())
    dict_values = list(dictionary.values())
    for x in range(len(dict_keys)):
        df.loc[df[colsource]==dict_keys[x], coltarget] = dict_values[x]
    return(df)
```
